With about 1.6 billion followers, almost a quarter of earth's population,[36][2][37] Islam is the second-largest and the fastest-growing religion in the world.[38] due primarily to the young age and high fertility rate of Muslims,[39] with Muslim having a rate of (3.1) compared to the world average of (2.5). According to the same study religious switching has no impact on Muslim population, since the number of people who embrace Islam and those who leave Islam are roughly equal.[39]
